  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and organizations dedicated to combating money laundering:\n\n1. Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- An intergovernmental organization that sets global standards\n- Develops recommendations for preventing money laundering\n- Most countries follow its guidelines\n\n2. United Nations Conventions\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- UN Convention Against Corruption\n- Provide frameworks for international cooperation\n\n3. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- Establishes international banking regulations\n- Provides guidelines for preventing money laundering\n\n4. International Monetary Fund (IMF)\n- Helps countries develop anti-money laundering policies\n- Provides technical assistance\n\n5. Egmont Group\n- International network of financial intelligence units\n- Facilitates information sharing between countries\n\n6. European Union Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Comprehensive regulations for EU member states\n- Regularly updated to address emerging risks\n\nMost countries have national laws implementing these international standards, requiring financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nThese laws aim to prevent criminal activities and track the flow of illegal funds globally.",
